  "doc_id": "25825",
  "text": "Here we harnessed the power of trait extremes [CITATION_1] , coupled with a pooled genome wide association strategy (9) to approach genetic determinants of human hypertension. Exploiting the statistical power that is possible with a very large sample size, we selected individuals through a sampling design with the power to detect small contributions to BP variation, ascertaining individuals within the highest and lowest 5th percentiles of BP in a primary care setting in southern California with a large community database (>53,000 subjects) of men and women whose BP was measured at routine health maintenance visits. Genomic DNA pooling is an effective initial strategy that has been successful in detecting genetic associations for amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (39), memory performance (40), progressive supranuclear palsy (41), multiple sclerosis [CITATION_2] , and melanoma [CITATION_3] .",
